the accessible education center (aec) collaborates with university housing to determine and prescribe housing accommodations based on students functional limitations. students requesting housing accommodations, must register with aec by completing our application online viamyaec. students are required to submit documentation verifying their disability; documentation must include how the students functional limitations that impact their ability to live in university housing.please note that university housing is heavily impacted; all sjsu students applying to live in university housing need to meet the housing application deadline. accommodations will be considered based on housing availability for students who apply after the housing deadline.students with food allergies are encouraged to sign up on the upper righ-hand corner ofcampus dining's wesbite, so campus dining can best communiate with students when eating at the commons.office emailsstaff directoryadministration building(adm)room 110accessible education centersan jos state universityone washington squaresan jose, ca 95192-0168mon: 9 am - 5 pmtues: 9 am - 5 pmwed: 10 am - 5 pmthurs: 9 am - 4 pmfri: 9 am - 4 pm